<subSubSection id="C3114BE55C4BFFC8FF58FCD2AED2FE25" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C4BFFCBFF58FCD2ADD0FC85" blockId="1.[151,1436,786,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C4BFFCBFF58FCD2AD7DFCDC" bold="true" box="[151,273,786,811]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dark brown to black; palpus, legs and halter yellow; frons setose; face glabrous; proboscis around 0.75 length of head height; acrostichal setae biserial; scutum with four darker longitudinal bands; fore tarsomere 1 not swollen; abdomen silvery.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C4BFFCBFF08FCBEAE82FAB1" blockId="1.[151,1436,786,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C4BFFCBFF08FCBEAD12FC60" bold="true" box="[199,382,894,919]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Re-description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54B0A6CC5C4BFFCBFE4BFCBFAD80FC60" box="[388,492,895,919]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Holotype</typeStatus>
female. Body 
<quantity id="4CF3B58B5C4BFFCBFD5FFCBFAE85FC61" box="[656,745,895,919]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; wing 
<quantity id="4CF3B58B5C4BFFCBFCFDFCBFAFEBFC61" box="[818,903,895,919]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="57" unit="mm" value="5.7">5.7 mm</quantity>
long. Head (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFBD7FCBFA835FC60" box="[1048,1113,895,919]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Dichoptic; ommatidia subequal. Frons (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFEF9FC62AD10FC4D" box="[310,380,930,954]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) grey pruinose, as wide as ocellar tubercle, slightly higher than greatest width, subparallelsided, with short distinct lateroclinate setae, with 6–7 setae at inner row and 2 at outer row. Face as high as frons, but wider, divergent at ventral margin, grey pruinose. Palpus (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFCA3FC2AAFDEFBF5" box="[876,946,1002,1026]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) yellow, slender, with distinct clear setae, except for few robust elongate black setae. Proboscis (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFD3AFBCFAF59FBD0" box="[757,821,1039,1063]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) around 0.75 head height, labrum black, shiny. Ocellar tubercle slightly protruding, ocelli reddish glassy; anterior ocellar seta robust, divergent, and 3–4 short, aligned, distinct posterior setae. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFDDEFB97AE3EFB98" box="[529,594,1111,1135]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) with scape and pedicel brown to yellow, postpedicel velvety matte black, 1.5X longer than length of scape and pedicel combined and around 2.2X longer than apparently two segmented stylus. Segment 1 of stylus apparently masked by segment 2, segment two around 0.25 postpedicel length and slightly longer than thin segment 3. Postcranium (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFDA4FB02AEC3FB2D" box="[619,687,1218,1242]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) brown, densely grey pruinose, setae of upper half black and more robust than slender and white setae of lower half; postocular setae medium sized as shown in 
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFB77FB27A891FB08" box="[1208,1277,1255,1279]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
; vertical setae subequal to adjacent postocular; occipital setae multiserial, misaligned. Supracervical plate with 1–2 short setae dorsally. Gena and postgena with slender white setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C4BFFCBFF08FA92AF56F958" blockId="1.[151,1436,786,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
Thorax (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFEE7FA92AD00FA9D" box="[296,364,1362,1386]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Dark brown to black, grey pruinose. Postalar lobe slightly yellowish-brown; scutum with dark longitudinal band between acrostichal and dorsocentral rows and between dorsocentral and supra-alar rows, latter band less conspicuous. Chaetotaxy: 4 black antepronotals, lateral more robust; around 15 subequal, clear postpronotals, except 2 dark posterior setae slightly more robust; 5–6 slender, white proepisternals; around 15 slender, white proepimerals; distinct biserial acrostichals with incomplete internal row, posterior setae damaged; dorsocentrals longer than acrostichals, uniserial medially, misaligned anterior and posteriorly where they appear to be biserial, posterior setae more robust, notably latter; 5–6 short intra-alar presuturals, one of them slightly more robust and one placed near transverse suture; 2 intra-alar postsuturals; 4–5 aligned supra-alar presuturals, posterior setae more robust; 4 aligned supraalar postsuturals, latter stout; 3 robust notopleurals and several slender; 1 robust postalar, 1 short and slender placed anteriorly; 2 scutellars, apical probably convergent or crossed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C4BFFCBFF08F97BAF57F838" blockId="1.[151,1436,786,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">
Legs (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFEC3F97AAD15F925" box="[268,377,1722,1746]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Figs. 6–8</figureCitation>
). Yellow, with grey pruinosity more distinct on coxae and femora; trochanter with small apical black spot ventrallly, setae short, some of them more robust and black. Fore tibia (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFBE5F91FA801F900" box="[1066,1133,1759,1783]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) with 1 basal dorsal seta, 1 posterodorsal on basal third, 1 anterodorsal on middle third, 1 posterior, 1 apical anterodorsal, 2 posteroventrals on distal third. Mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFE5AF8E7ADB5F8C8" box="[405,473,1831,1855]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with 3 anterodorsals, 2 on basal half and 1 distal and 3 posterodorsals, 1 submedian, 1 distal and 1 slender between them. Hind tibia (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C4BFFCBFD79F88AAE94F895" box="[694,760,1866,1890]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="57">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) with 6–7 dorsal setae, 2–3 basal more slender, 3 anterodorsals, 2 on basal third and 1 apical; 5 anteroventrals, with 2 on middle third and 3 on distal third, 2 of them set closely together; hind tarsomere 1 with 1 dorsal and 1 ventral seta, both placed near base. Fore tarsomere 1 not swollen, narrower than tibia, about 0.5X length of fore tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C48FFC8FF08FF57AC85FF0D" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">
Wing (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C48FFC8FED7FF57AD1CFF58" box="[280,368,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="12.[151,261,579,602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetId="figure-502@12.[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Wings. 70, Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀; 71, H. barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 72, H. carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 73, H. elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂; 74, H. gymnaspis Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 75, H. xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248054/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). Hyaline with brown veins; costal vein with 1 robust basal seta (not illustrated in figure); pterostigma tenuous, yellow, occupying apex of costal cell and part of cell r 
<subScript id="178F1A2B5C48FFC8FC29FF0BAF82FF2E" attach="left" box="[998,1006,203,217]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">1</subScript>
. A 
<subScript id="178F1A2B5C48FFC8FBDFFF0BA874FF2E" attach="left" box="[1040,1048,203,217]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">1</subScript>
almost entirely evanescent. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C48FFC8FF08FEC7ADC4FEB5" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Abdomen yellow in certain angles, distinctly silvery grey pruinose; setae clear, more slender laterally on anterior tergites. Sternites yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C48FFC8FF08FE8FAEAAFE7D" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C48FFC8FE9DFE8FADBCFE90" box="[338,464,335,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Figs. 9–10</figureCitation>
). Brown, slightly grey pruinose. Tergite 8 shorter than sternite 8 (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C48FFC8FB00FE8FA97AFE90" box="[1231,1302,335,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1522,1545]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,983,1506]" captionTargetId="figure-515@2.[151,1436,974,1507]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀. 1, head, lateral view; 2, frons, frontal view; 3, palpus, lateral view; 4, postcranium, posterolateral view; 5, thorax, dorsal view; 6, left fore leg, posterior view; 7, left mid leg, posterior view; 8, left hind leg, anterior view; 9–10, pieces strongly cleared with edges rather unclear; 9, tergite and sternite 8, tergite and sternite 10 and cercus, lateral view; 10, sternite 8, sternite 9 and cercus, ventral view. Abbreviations: ce = cercus, T = tergite, St = sternite. Scale bars: 1, 6–8 = 1.0 mm; 2–5 = 0.5 mm; 9–10 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248042" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248042/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); tergite 10 elongate; cercus short, slightly acuminate distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C48FFC8FF08FE57ADE8FE58" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,935]" box="[199,388,407,431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
