<subSubSection id="C3114BE55C48FFC8FF08FD8AA903FC50" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C48FFC8FF08FD8AA903FC50" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FF08FD8AAD25FD94" bold="true" box="[199,329,586,611]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" reason="1">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FE80FD8BAE25FD94" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[335,585,587,611]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifera">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FE80FD8BAE25FD94" box="[335,585,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">Hilarempis argentifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apparently belongs to a group together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FBFDFD8BA946FD95" authority="Collin, 1933" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[1074,1322,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosa">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FBFDFD8BA8F0FD94" box="[1074,1180,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">H. dolosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A659F5C48FFC8FB6CFD8AA946FD95" author="Collin, J. E." box="[1187,1322,586,610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin, 1933</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FAF7FD8BAD73FD70" authority="Collin, 1933" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facilis">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FAF7FD8BA9F7FD94" box="[1336,1435,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">H. facilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A659F5C48FFC8FF58FDAFAD73FD70" author="Collin, J. E." box="[151,287,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin, 1933</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FE9BFDB0AE1BFD70" authority="Collin, 1933" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[340,631,623,647]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="propinqua">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FE9BFDB0AD8BFD70" box="[340,487,624,647]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">H. propinqua</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A659F5C48FFC8FE22FDAFAE1BFD70" author="Collin, J. E." box="[493,631,623,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin, 1933</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, all sharing four longitudinal bands on the mesonotum, dorsocentral setae more than uniserial and female cercus downcurved. It differs from all of these species by abdominal tergites yellow from certain angles and sternites yellow. Using the key in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A659F5C48FFC8FCC0FD77AFC8FD38" author="Collin, J. E." box="[783,932,695,719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin (1933)</bibRefCitation>
, the female specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FB7EFD78A927FD38" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1909" box="[1201,1355,695,719]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentifera">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FB7EFD78A927FD38" box="[1201,1355,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">H. argentifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
runs to couplet 18 of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FEE4FD1BADF9FD04" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[299,405,731,755]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosa">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FEE4FD1BADF9FD04" box="[299,405,731,755]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">H. dolosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from the latter species by the postpedicel 3.1X as long as deep at widest part (2.0X in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FF58FCC0AD6CFCE0" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[151,256,767,791]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosa">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FF58FCC0AD6CFCE0" box="[151,256,767,791]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">H. dolosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 2.5X in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FEBFFCC0ADBFFCE0" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[368,467,767,791]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="facilis">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FEBFFCC0ADBFFCE0" box="[368,467,767,791]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">H. facilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 1.5X in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FDADFCC0AE9FFCE0" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[610,755,768,791]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="propinqua">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C48FFC8FDADFCC0AE9FFCE0" box="[610,755,768,791]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="58">H. propinqua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The proportion between postpedicel and stylus is rather identical in all species cited above. One other more reliable character that can be compared among these four species was used under the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C48FFC8FE8EFC88ADC1FCA8" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[321,429,839,863]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolosa">
